raspberrypi-firmware (9.20200616-4.19.95+revpi1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Public 4.19 release for the upcoming 6/2020 image.

 -- Kunbus <admin@kunbus.de>  Tue, 16 Jun 2020 13:15:00 +0200

raspberrypi-firmware (9.20200120-4.19.95+revpi1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Fixups for RevPi Connect Flat:
    
    Compile pca953x driver into kernel proper and not as a module
    to speed up probing of UART drivers which require access to
    rs485 termination GPIOs.
    
    Avoid failure of assigning 1 as number of runtime 8250 UARTs
    caused by comment.
    
    UART1 is controlled by the core clock.   Downclocking changes
    the baudrate and garbles I/O.  Avoid by defaulting to "performance"
    cpufreq governor.  This ensures that UART1 is usable as console.

 -- Kunbus <admin@kunbus.de>  Mon, 20 Jan 2020 15:00:00 +0100

raspberrypi-firmware (9.20190927-4.19.29+revpi1) stable; urgency=medium

  * New upstream release based on v4.19
  * Add support for RevPi Connect Flat

 -- Kunbus <admin@kunbus.de>  Fri, 27 Sep 2019 15:30:00 +0200

raspberrypi-firmware (9.20200228-4.9.76+revpi1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Quiesce IRQs left enabled by bootloader to fix lockups
  * Drive mux GPIO low on RevPi Connect via dt-blob.bin
    to work around missing pulldown on hardware rev 06
  * Update dt-blob.bin on package installation
  * piControl: Support RevPi Connect Flat
  * piControl: Support I/O module status
  * piControl: Support seek ioctl

 -- Kunbus <admin@kunbus.de>  Fri, 28 Feb 2020 15:15:00 +0100

